✅ private String url;
This means only the BaseTest class itself can access url.

You would need to create a getter method like getUrl() if you want to use it in another class.

Best for full encapsulation, but less flexible if you want to use the URL in your test or page classes.

✅ protected String url;
This means url can be used in BaseTest and also in any class that extends BaseTest (like your test classes).

This is the most common choice if your test classes need to access the URL directly.

Keeps it hidden from outside classes unless they extend BaseTest.

✅ public String url;
This means any class anywhere can access the url directly.

It's the most open, but not recommended, because it breaks encapsulation and makes your code harder to manage later.

✅ Recommendation:
Use **protected** for url in BaseTest, just like your driver, so your test classes can access it safely but it’s still not fully public.

